The Herald President Mnangagwa has sworn-in Justice Loice Matanda-Moyo as the new chairperson of the Zimbabwe Anti-Corruption (ZACC) Commission at a brief ceremony held at State House today. <img class="wp-image-433220 size-large" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/05/Matanda-Moyo-1-680x420.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="420" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/05/Matanda-Moyo-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2019/05/Matanda-Moyo-1-360x222.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa is pictured with Justice Matanda-Moyo during a photo session soon after the swearing-in ceremony. Justice Matanda-Moyo is expected to give fresh impetus to the nation’s drive to eradicate the scourge that has assumed epidemic proportions across the country’s economic sectors. (more to follow)